Quick mv -i and cp -i aliases:<p><pre><code>  alias mvi=&quot;mv -i&quot;
  alias cpi=&quot;cp -i&quot;
</code></pre>
Truncate a file to empty:<p><pre><code>  alias zeroout=&quot;truncate -s 0&quot;</code></pre>

I have the same script, calling it nnohup in my ~/bin folder.<p>Common GUI programs I often launch from the command line I put an alias in my .bashrc for. e.g.<p><pre><code>  alias thg=&quot;~/bin/nnohup /usr/bin/thg&quot;
  alias rabbitvcs=&quot;~/bin/nnohup /usr/bin/rabbitvcs&quot;
  alias meld=&quot;~/bin/nnohup /usr/bin/meld&quot;
  alias xnview=&quot;~/bin/nnohup /usr/bin/xnview&quot;
  alias dolphin=&quot;~/bin/nnohup /usr/bin/dolphin&quot;
  alias vlc=&quot;~/bin/nnohup /usr/bin/vlc&quot;</code></pre>
